Thanks [~jlowe] and [~bibinchundatt]
From AMLauncher,
{code}
        launch();
        handler.handle(new RMAppAttemptEvent(application.getAppAttemptId(),
            RMAppAttemptEventType.LAUNCHED));
{code}
we raise LAUNCHED event to attempt as soon as we launch AM container. I think mostly this event must be in central dispatcher queue (considering queue is overloaded) far ahead than REGISTERED event raised from {{ApplicationMasterService.registerApplicationMaster}}. Now in the above mentioned {{launch}}, if the response was received slowly from {{containerMgrProxy}}, there is a window with which LAUNCHED may be delayed  from launcher side. I am not very sure though since it may be a n/w delay and heavily loaded queue in dispatcher together can come and cause  this.
